  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women HRDs in the Amazon: building alternatives to violence</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">See Theory of Change attached in Reporting - Documents</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will address violence against women human rights defenders in the context of conflict around the control of natural resources in the Amazon, specifically related to the construction of dams in the region. In order to combat such violence, the project aims to develop community-based strategies of protection that are not only sensitive to the gendered dimensions of the risks WHRDs face but also help to reduce a sense of isolation among individuals and build solidarity. The project will work with target communities affected by mega projects in the states of Par&#xE1; and Rondonia strengthening capacity-building to identify, monitor and address violence. The objective is to promote a holistic approach to protection which considers gender specificities and geographic isolation, documents violations faced by WHRDs using an intersectional lens, supports women&#x2019;s own perception of the risks they face, promote the work of WHRDs among local and national stakeholders, build protection tools that include dimensions of self-care and collective well-being, and build spaces that are conducive to enhancing protection to WHRDs.</narrative>
  </description>
